agentMibCapabilityEntry.description: A MIB capability entry contains objects describing a particular MIB supported by this agent.

agentMibCapabilityVersion.description: The version of the MIB specified in this entry.

agentStatusConsoleInUse.name: agentStatusConsoleInUse
agentStatusConsoleInUse.description: This indicates whether the console is currently in-use.

agentStatusSaveCfg.name: agentStatusSaveCfg
agentStatusSaveCfg.description: This indicates the status of the device configuration. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. proceeding(2) - the device configuration is being currently saved into the NV-RAM. completed(3) - all of the device configuration parameters have been saved into NV-RAM. failed(4) - The process to save device configuration has failed.

agentStatusFileTransfer.name: agentStatusFileTransfer
agentStatusFileTransfer.description: The status of the firmware download control. If the value is 'other', this means the firmware has not been updated since the device started up.

agentCPUutilizationIn5sec.name: agentCPUutilizationIn5sec
agentCPUutilizationIn5sec.description: The unit of time is 5 seconds. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

agentCPUutilizationIn1min.name: agentCPUutilizationIn1min
agentCPUutilizationIn1min.description: The unit of time is 1 minute. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

agentCPUutilizationIn5min.name: agentCPUutilizationIn5min
agentCPUutilizationIn5min.description: The unit of time is 5 minutes. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

agentPORTutilizationTable.name: agentPORTutilizationTable
agentPORTutilizationTable.description: The table specifies the port's utilization function.

agentPORTutilizationEntry.name: agentPORTutilizationEntry
agentPORTutilizationEntry.description: A list of information about the port's utilization function.

agentPORTutilizationProtIndex.name: agentPORTutilizationProtIndex
agentPORTutilizationProtIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.

agentPORTutilizationTX.name: agentPORTutilizationTX
agentPORTutilizationTX.description: The real-time gauges of transmitted frames on the specific port.

agentPORTutilizationRX.name: agentPORTutilizationRX
agentPORTutilizationRX.description: The real-time gauges of recieved frames on the specific port.

agentPORTutilizationUtil.name: agentPORTutilizationUtil
agentPORTutilizationUtil.description: The real-time percentage of the port statistics.

agentDRAMutilizationEntry.name: agentDRAMutilizationEntry
agentDRAMutilizationEntry.description: A list of information about DRAM memory.

agentDRAMutilizationUnitID.name: agentDRAMutilizationUnitID
agentDRAMutilizationUnitID.description: Specifies the unit ID. If the ID equals zero, it means the current device.

agentDRAMutilizationTotalDRAM.name: agentDRAMutilizationTotalDRAM
agentDRAMutilizationTotalDRAM.description: The size of the total DRAM memory.

agentDRAMutilizationUsedDRAM.name: agentDRAMutilizationUsedDRAM
agentDRAMutilizationUsedDRAM.description: The size of the used DRAM memory.

agentDRAMutilization.name: agentDRAMutilization
agentDRAMutilization.description: The percentage of used DRAM memory of the total DRAM memory available. The value will be between 0%(idle) and 100%(very busy).

agentSerialNumber.name: agentSerialNumber
agentSerialNumber.description: A text string containing the serial number of this device.

agentBscSwFileTable.name: agentBscSwFileTable
agentBscSwFileTable.description: A list of MIB basic config entries that support file update by this agent.

agentBscSwFileEntry.name: agentBscSwFileEntry
agentBscSwFileEntry.description: A basic configuration entry contains objects describing a particular MIB supported by this agent.

agentBscSwFileIndex.name: agentBscSwFileIndex
agentBscSwFileIndex.description: The table index for the file entry.

agentBscSwFileDscr.name: agentBscSwFileDscr
agentBscSwFileDscr.description: The description for the purpose of the software file in this entry. Note: For systems which do not support change of this object, setting values to this object will cause the system to return a bad-value error message.

agentBscSwFileAddr.name: agentBscSwFileAddr
agentBscSwFileAddr.description: The IP address where the file to be downloaded is located, or the IP address where the file will be uploaded to.

agentBscSwFileTransferType.name: agentBscSwFileTransferType
agentBscSwFileTransferType.description: The channel through which the file will be downloaded or uploaded. Note: For systems which do not support all channels, setting values to the unsupported channel will cause the system to return a bad-value error message.

agentBscSwFile.name: agentBscSwFile
agentBscSwFile.description: The name of the file to be downloaded from the TFTP server, or to be uploaded to.

agentBscSwFileLocateId.name: agentBscSwFileLocateId
agentBscSwFileLocateId.description: This object describes the type of the file. runtime-code(1), log-file(2), cfg-file(3) Note: For a system which does not support change of this object, setting a value to this object will cause the system to return a bad-value error message.

agentBscSwFileLoadType.name: agentBscSwFileLoadType
agentBscSwFileLoadType.description: This object allows the user to select the download or upload function for the file. Note: For a system which does not support change of this object, setting a value to this object will cause the system to return a bad-value error message.

agentBscSwFileCtrl.name: agentBscSwFileCtrl
agentBscSwFileCtrl.description: This object allows the user to download runtime software. The setting will take effect when the system restarts. See Note (1) below Note: For systems which do not support change of this object to some value, setting these values causes the system to return bad-value error messages. start - start to action. delete(4) - delete the firmware by indicated firmware ID. config-as-bootup-fw(5) - configured as bootup firmware by indicated firmware(ID).

agentBscSwFileBIncrement.name: agentBscSwFileBIncrement
agentBscSwFileBIncrement.description: The object indicates whether the previous configuration will be valid or not after downloading the configuration file. True: keep valid False: erase.

agentMultiImageCtrlID.name: agentMultiImageCtrlID
agentMultiImageCtrlID.description: The section ID of the firmware image.

agentFileTransfer.name: agentFileTransfer
agentFileTransfer.description: This object will execute the download or upload action. If start(2), it will begin to download/upload, but no reset follows. If start-and-reset(3), then the reset will activate after download or upload. No action if (4). Note: Because these functions will be limited by the system support, some of the selected items will be invalid. When the user selects one of the items, it will respond with bad-value status.

agentSystemReset.name: agentSystemReset
agentSystemReset.description: This object indicates the agent system reset state. Setting this object to no-reset(4) has no effect. Setting this object to cold-start(2) or warm-start(3) will reset the agent. The agent always returns no-reset(4) when this object is read.

agentRs232PortConfig.name: agentRs232PortConfig
agentRs232PortConfig.description: This object indicates the RS-232C mode when the device has restarted.

agentOutOfBandBaudRateConfig.name: agentOutOfBandBaudRateConfig
agentOutOfBandBaudRateConfig.description: This object allows the user to the specify out-of-band baud rate. It will take effect when the system is restarted. Note: Because these functions will be limited by the system support, some of the selected items will be invalid. When the user selects one of the items, it will respond with a bad-value status.

agentSaveCfg.name: agentSaveCfg
agentSaveCfg.description: As the object is set to 'set(3)', the current device configuration will be saved into to NV-RAM.

swMultiImageInfoEntry.name: swMultiImageInfoEntry
swMultiImageInfoEntry.description: A list of information about multiple image management.

swMultiImageInfoID.name: swMultiImageInfoID
swMultiImageInfoID.description: The section ID of the firmware image.

swMultiImageVersion.name: swMultiImageVersion
swMultiImageVersion.description: The record of the downloaded firmware version.

swMultiImageSize.name: swMultiImageSize
swMultiImageSize.description: The record of the downloaded firmware size.

swMultiImageUpdateTime.name: swMultiImageUpdateTime
swMultiImageUpdateTime.description: The record of the firmware updated time.

swMultiImageFrom.name: swMultiImageFrom
swMultiImageFrom.description: The record of the IP address of the TFTP server.

swMultiImageSendUser.name: swMultiImageSendUser
swMultiImageSendUser.description: The record of the user who downloaded the firmware.

agentTrustHostIPSubnetMask.name: agentTrustHostIPSubnetMask

agentTrustHostForHTTPS.name: agentTrustHostForHTTPS
agentTrustHostForHTTPS.description: Specifies the trusted host for HTTPS.

agentFDBClearAllState.name: agentFDBClearAllState
agentFDBClearAllState.description: Used to clear all FDB entries.

agentARPClearAllState.name: agentARPClearAllState
agentARPClearAllState.description: Used to clear all ARP entries.

agentGratuitousARPSendIpifStatusUpState.name: agentGratuitousARPSendIpifStatusUpState
agentGratuitousARPSendIpifStatusUpState.description: It is used to enable/disable sending of gratuitous ARP request packets while IPIF interface come up. This is used to automatically announce the interface's IP address to other nodes. By default, the state is enabled, and only one ARP packet will be broadcast.

agentGratuitousARPSendDupIpDetectedState.name: agentGratuitousARPSendDupIpDetectedState
agentGratuitousARPSendDupIpDetectedState.description: It is used to enable/disable sending of gratuitous ARP request packets while a duplicate IP is detected. By default, the state is enabled. The duplicate IP detected means that the system received a ARP request packet that is sent by an IP address that matches the system's own IP address. In this case, the system knows that somebody out there is using an IP address that is in conflict with the system. In order to reclaim the correct host of this IP address, the system can send out the gratuitous ARP request packet for this duplicate IP address.

agentGratuitousARPLearningState.name: agentGratuitousARPLearningState
agentGratuitousARPLearningState.description: It is used to enable/disable learning of an ARP entry in the ARP cache based on the received gratuitous ARP packet. If the switch receives a gratuitous ARP request/reply packet and the sender's IP address is in its ARP table, it should update the ARP entry. By default, the state is disabled.

agentGratuitousARPEntry.name: agentGratuitousARPEntry
agentGratuitousARPEntry.description: A list of information from the Gratuitous ARP Table.

agentGratuitousARPInterfaceName.name: agentGratuitousARPInterfaceName
agentGratuitousARPInterfaceName.description: The name of the IP interface.

agentGratuitousARPPeriodicalSendInterval.name: agentGratuitousARPPeriodicalSendInterval
agentGratuitousARPPeriodicalSendInterval.description: It is used to configure the interval for the periodic sending of gratuitous ARP request packets. 0 means not send gratuitous ARP periodically.

agentGratuitousARPTrapState.name: agentGratuitousARPTrapState
agentGratuitousARPTrapState.description: It indicates the state of the gratuitous ARP trap. The switch can trap the IP conflict event to inform the administrator. By default, the trap is disabled.

agentGratuitousARPLogState.name: agentGratuitousARPLogState
agentGratuitousARPLogState.description: It indicates the state of the gratuitous Log trap. The switch can log the IP conflict event to inform the administrator. By default, the event log is enabled.

agentReset.name: agentReset
agentReset.description: Used to reset all switch parameters. none(1) : No action. This is the default value of this object. config(2): All parameters are reset to default settings, but the device will neither save nor reboot. system(3): All parameters are reset to default settings. The switch will then do a factory reset, save, and reboot. reset(4) : All parameters will be reset to default settings except IP address, user account, and history log, but the device will neither save nor reboot. system-exlude-vlan(5) : All parameters are reset to default settings except VLAN. The switch will then save its settings and reboot. system-_exlude-ip(6) : All parameters are reset to default settings except IP address. The switch will then save its settings and reboot. system-exlude-vlan-ip(7): All parameters are reset to default settings except VLAN and IP address. The switch will then save its settings and reboot.

agentSnmpTrapState.name: agentSnmpTrapState
agentSnmpTrapState.description: This object indicates the state of snmp trap is enabled or disabled.

agentTrustHostDelAllState.name: agentTrustHostDelAllState
agentTrustHostDelAllState.description: Used to delete all trusted host entries.

agentIpNumOfIf.name: agentIpNumOfIf
agentIpNumOfIf.description: The total number of IP interfaces supported by this agent.

agentIpTftpServerAddr.name: agentIpTftpServerAddr
agentIpTftpServerAddr.description: The IP Address of the TFTP server.

agentIpGetIpFrom.name: agentIpGetIpFrom
agentIpGetIpFrom.description: This object indicates whether the agent get its system IP address from BOOTP/DHCP server at start up.

systemTrapsSeverity.name: systemTrapsSeverity
systemTrapsSeverity.description: Indicates the level of system severity control. The system has a severity level control and each trap should be associated with a severity control. When a trap event occurs and its severity is higher than the system severity control level, the trap works as defined. If the event severity is lower than the system severity control level, the event is ignored as if it did not occur.

systemLogsSeverity.name: systemLogsSeverity
systemLogsSeverity.description: Indicates the level of system severity control. The system has a severity level control and each log should be associated with a severity control. When a log event occurs and its severity is higher than the system severity control level, the log works as defined. If the event severity is lower than the system severity control level, the event is ignored as if it did not occur.

agentGratuitousARPTrap.name: agentGratuitousARPTrap
agentGratuitousARPTrap.description: The trap is sent when there is an IP address conflict.

agentGratuitousARPIpAddr.name: agentGratuitousARPIpAddr
agentGratuitousARPIpAddr.description: Duplicate IP address with the switch.

agentGratuitousARPMacAddr.name: agentGratuitousARPMacAddr
agentGratuitousARPMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the device which has the duplicate IP address.

agentGratuitousARPPortNumber.name: agentGratuitousARPPortNumber
agentGratuitousARPPortNumber.description: It indicates the portNum with a string, For example, if the device is in standalone mode, and the port number is 23, the string should be 23. If the device is in stack mode, and the unit ID is 2, and the port number is 3, the string should be 2:3.
